#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:15
msgid "Use the plugins toolkit instead of importing CKAN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:17
msgid ""
"Try to limit your extension to interacting with CKAN only through CKAN's "
":doc:`plugin interfaces <plugin-interfaces>` and :doc:`plugins toolkit "
"<plugins-toolkit>`. It's a good idea to keep your extension code separate "
"from CKAN as much as possible, so that internal changes in CKAN from one "
"release to the next don't break your extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:26
msgid "Don't edit CKAN's database tables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:28
msgid ""
"An extension can create its own tables in the CKAN database, but it should "
"*not* write to core CKAN tables directly, add columns to core tables, or use"
" foreign keys against core tables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:35
msgid "Implement each plugin class in a separate Python module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:37
msgid ""
"This keeps CKAN's plugin loading order simple, see :ref:`ckan.plugins`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:44
msgid "Names of config settings should include the name of the extension"
msgstr ""

#: ../../extensions/best-practices.rst:46
msgid ""
